  <!-- About the Venue -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>🏛️ About the Venue</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>The <strong>Junipero Serra Museum</strong> is a stunning historic landmark in <strong>Presidio Park</strong>, perched on a hilltop overlooking Mission Valley and the San Diego River. Built in 1929 in Spanish Colonial Revival style, the museum marks the site where Father Junipero Serra established the first Spanish mission in California in 1769.</p>
      <div class="highlight">
        <strong>🌅 Why it's special:</strong> Gorgeous panoramic views of San Diego, beautiful Spanish architecture, lush gardens, and a sense of history that makes for an unforgettable wedding backdrop. The hilltop setting means golden hour photos will be incredible.
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">🏔️ Hilltop Views</span>
        <span class="tag">🏛️ Historic Landmark</span>
        <span class="tag">🌿 Garden Setting</span>
        <span class="tag">📸 Photo Paradise</span>
        <span class="tag">🌇 Golden Hour Magic</span>
        <span class="tag">🎭 Spanish Colonial Style</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

