          <span class="li-icon">🏛️</span>
          <div><strong><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Marston+House+3525+7th+Ave+San+Diego+CA+92103" target="_blank" style="color:var(--wedding);text-decoration:none;">Marston House</a></strong><br>3525 7th Ave, San Diego, CA 92103 · <a href="tel:+16192979327" style="color:var(--text-mid);text-decoration:none;">(619) 297-9327</a><br>Historic Arts &amp; Crafts mansion from 1905.</div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="li-icon">⚓</span>
          <div><strong><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Embarcadero+1492+N+Harbor+Dr+San+Diego+CA+92101" target="_blank" style="color:var(--wedding);text-decoration:none;">Embarcadero</a></strong><br>1492 N Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92101<br>Cruise-ship hub with Seaport Village (seafood, souvenir shops), The Headquarters (chic eateries, boutiques in an old police command post), USS Midway Museum (former aircraft carrier with flight simulators and restored planes), Waterfront Park with ocean views.</div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="li-icon">🌿</span>
          <div><strong><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Balboa+Park+San+Diego+CA" target="_blank" style="color:var(--wedding);text-decoration:none;">Balboa Park</a></strong> <span style="color:var(--sunset);font-size:0.78rem;">★ Nancy's pick</span><br>San Diego, CA · <a href="tel:+161****0512" style="color:var(--text-mid);text-decoration:none;">(619) 239-0512</a><br>San Diego's version of Central Park, but bigger 😎. 1,200 acres, 18 museums, gardens, hiking trails, and the world-famous San Diego Zoo. Pack a lunch and sit where the planes fly ~50 ft overhead descending into Lindbergh Field. The Prado (1914/15 promenade, expanded 1934/35) has museums and Spanish Colonial architecture from the Panama-California Exposition.</div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="li-icon">🗼</span>
          <div><strong><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Cabrillo+National+Monument+1800+Cabrillo+Memorial+Dr+San+Diego+CA+92106" target="_blank" style="color:var(--wedding);text-decoration:none;">Cabrillo National Monument &amp; Lighthouse</a></strong> <span style="color:var(--sunset);font-size:0.78rem;">★ Nancy's pick</span><br>1800 Cabrillo Memorial Dr, San Diego, CA 92106<br>National monument on the tip of Point Loma peninsula ($15-20 entry). 270° views of downtown San Diego, Coronado Island, north beaches, and out to the Pacific. Tide pools at the base of Point Loma are open to park visitors.</div>
        </li>
        <li>
